DL: https://adoptium.net/
DL: https://developer.android.com/studio (https://redirector.gvt1.com/edgedl/android/studio/install/2024.3.1.15/android-studio-2024.3.1.15-windows.exe)

Edit Environment Variables:
Search for "Environment Variables" in the Windows search bar and select "Edit the system environment variables".
Click the "Environment Variables..." button.   
In the "System variables" section (or "User variables" if you only want it for your user), find the Path variable, select it, and click "Edit...".   
Click "New" and paste the full path to the JDK's bin directory you found earlier. 
(C:\Program Files\Eclipse Adoptium\jdk-21.0.7.6-hotspot\bin) & (C:\Users\%username%\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\build-tools\36.0.0)
Click "OK" on all the dialog boxes to save the changes.
IMPORTANT: You must close your current Command Prompt/PowerShell and open a new one for the PATH changes to take effect.
